"{\"uid\": \"salon.com-2024-08-10-australia-put-a-unique-spin-on-breakdancing-at-the-olympics-leading-to-disappointing-ridicule\", \"text\": \"Rachael Gunn, a 36-year-old\\u00c2\\u00a0lecturer at Macquarie University in Sydney, delivered a historic display at the ParisOlympics, representing Australia as their first competing breakdancer. And although Gunn (AKA \\\"Raygun\\\") lost all three of her group matches, she stole the show regardless.  Displaying a series of moves that could easily be mistaken as performance art, people on social media seemed to have a great deal of fun sharing clips of her at the games\\u00c2\\u00a0\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 referring to her in action as being \\\"possessed by the spirit of Julia Stiles in 'Save the Last Dance'\\\" as she debuted a maneuver now being referred to as \\\"the kangaroo\\\"\\u00c2\\u00a0\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 which Gunn herself took in stride, although Anna Meares,\\u00c2\\u00a0Australian two-time Olympic cycling gold medallist, viewed the reception as\\u00c2\\u00a0\\\"really disappointing.\\\"  In a quote obtained fromThe Guardian, Gunn comments on what could be seen as trolling for her unique breakdancing and costume choice\\u00c2\\u00a0\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 which some said resembled a fast food worker's uniform\\u00c2\\u00a0\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 saying,\\u00c2\\u00a0\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAll my moves are original.\\u00c2\\u00a0Creativity is really important to me. I go out there and I show my artistry.\\\" And there is certainly no doubt about that.  Australian Olympic breakdancer Rachael Gunn has a PhD in breakdancing and dance culture. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAll my moves are original,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she told reporters after her performance.pic.twitter.com/8to8quMx9y  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 Michael Nayna (@MikeNayna)August 10, 2024    \\\"I was never going to beat these girls on what they do best\\u00c2\\u00a0\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 the dynamic and the power moves\\u00c2\\u00a0\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 so I wanted to move differently\\u00c2\\u00a0\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 be artistic and creative\\u00c2\\u00a0\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 because how many chances do you get in a lifetime to do that on an international stage?\\\" Gunn said this week toBBC Sport.\\u00c2\\u00a0\\\"I was always the underdog and wanted to make my mark in a different way.\\\"  Gunn, who represented Australia in 2021, 2022 and 2023 at the World Breaking Championships, per CNBC, is known as the country's best female breakdancer. Which is fun.\\u00c2  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2026 Salon.com, LLC. Reproduction of material from any Salon pages without written permission is strictly prohibited. SALON \\u00c2\\u00ae is registered in the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office as a trademark of Salon.com, LLC. Associated Press articles: Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2016 The Associated Press. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed.  DMCA Policy  By subscribing, you agree that Salon will automatically charge you at the then-current rate (currently $9.95/month or $95/year) each month/year until you cancel. Log in to your account anytime to cancel prior to renewal date and avoid future charges.  Your current signup type is\"}"